dumpToGIF(25.10)                                              dumpToGIF(25.10)

Name
       dumpToGIF  -  Saves a snapshot of the current screen to a GIF file with
       the specified name in the current directory

Syntax
       dumpToGIF

       [-help]

       <filename>

       [-honor_umask]

       Saves a snapshot of the current screen to a GIF file with the specified
       name in the current directory. You can use this command at any stage of
       the design flow.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each dumpToGIF parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man dumpToGIF.

       <filename>
              Specifies the name of the output file as a string.

       -honor_umask
              Honors the umask settings while saving  the  GIF  file.  If  you
              specify  this  option, the permission of the saved GIF file will
              be set by subtracting the umask value from the  full  permission
              value.

              For  example,  if  the full permission setting of a file is 0666
              and the umask setting is 0022, the tool saves the GIF file  with
              the permission setting of 0666 - 0022, that is 0644.

Example
       The  following  example  captures  the  current  screen and saves it to
       <test1.gif> in the current directory.

       dumpToGif test1.gif

